channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: WATCH: ‘Building America’s Future’ Releases Powerful Ad, Slams Biden for Not Keeping American Women Safe
Army veteran running for Congress reveals plan to save America 'hijacked by left-wing lunatics'
item.description: Republican Abe Hamadeh, a U.S. Army intelligence officer and former prosecutor, is running to represent Arizona's 8th Congressional District.

item.title: FiveThirtyEight's Silver: Trump Now Clear Favorite
item.description: FiveThirtyEight founder Nate Silver, releasing his forecasting model for the 2024 presidential election, said Wednesday that the race "isn't a toss-up" and that the model is showing that former President Donald Trump is the clear favorite to win in November.

item.title: WATCH: Texas Judge Lays Blame for Brutal Rape and Murder of 12-Year-Old Jocelyn Nungary on Trump
Which Donald Trump will show up at Thursday night's CNN Presidential Debate?
item.description: It's the biggest question surrounding the first debate between President Biden and former President Trump in their 2024 election rematch — which version of Trump will show up?

item.title: Donald Trump Jr. Says No to VP Nikki Haley Idea
item.description: Donald Trump Jr. is pushing back on attempts to get his father, former President Donald Trump, to choose Nikki Haley as his running mate.

item.title: OOOPS. Supreme Court Posts Idaho Abortion Decision by Accident
House Democrats react to Jocelyn Nungaray murder: ‘I don’t know who she is’
item.description: House Democrats' reactions to the Jocelyn Nungaray murder have been caught on video Wednesday, with one lawmaker saying that "I don’t know who she is."

item.title: Watchdog: Just One-Third of Calls to IRS Reach a Human
item.description: If you are calling the IRS with tax questions, good luck talking to someone, according to the agency's taxpayer advocate watchdog service.

item.title: Nate Silver's First Presidential Election Forecast Is Out, and Democrats Are Losing Their Minds
Biden DHS reveals 50 migrants still at large as ISIS-affiliated smuggling network brings hundreds to US
item.description: DHS officials confirm to Fox News that over 400 migrants have been brought to the US via an ISIS-affiliated smuggling network, with 50 still at large.

item.title: Rep. Nehls to Newsmax: Trump Will Win Debate of Compare, Contrast
item.description: Donald Trump will easily win the presidential debate on Thursday night, because his policies are clearly superior to those of President Joe Biden's disastrous term in office, Rep. Troy Nehls told Newsmax on Wednesday.

item.title: Here's What Happens When Liberals Run the Military - Study Says It Is Now a 'Vast DEI Bureaucracy' Mess
Red states notify Biden admin of lawsuit over 'nonsensical' EV rule
item.description: A group of red states have notified the Biden administration they will challenge the latest fuel emissions restrictions, calling a new federal rule "nonsensical."

item.title: Speaker Johnson Vows to Sue to Access Hur Tapes
item.description: House Speaker Mike Johnson, R-La., said the House Judiciary Committee plans a lawsuit to force Attorney General Merrick Garland to turn over audio of President Joe Biden's interview with special counsel Robert Hur.
